🎯 What is JointForge?
JointForge is a Blender add-on that automatically creates precise keyed joints for splitting and reassembling 3D models. Perfect for:

🖨️ Large 3D prints - split models that exceed your printer's build volume

🔧 Multi-material prints - create assembly points for different materials

🎨 Paint-friendly models - split complex models for easier painting

📦 Storage optimization - create collapsible or modular designs

✨ Features
One-Click Operation - Select your mesh, choose a slicing plane, and generate matching joints instantly

Adjustable Joints - Customize key size, depth, and fit tolerance

Flexible Assignment - Choose which part gets the peg (additive) and which gets the notch (subtractive)

Non-Destructive - Original mesh remains untouched; new parts are created in a dedicated collection

Universal Application - Works with any mesh, not just organic shapes

🚀 Installation
Download JointForge.py

In Blender: Edit → Preferences → Add-ons → Install

Select the downloaded file and enable the add-on

Find "JointForge" in the 3D Viewport sidebar (N key)

📖 Usage
Basic Workflow
Prepare Your Model

Ensure your mesh is manifold (watertight)

Position your cutting plane where you want the split

Configure the Add-on

Key Size (mm) - Width of the square peg/hole

Key Depth (mm) - How deep the joint penetrates

Fit Gap (mm) - Clearance for easy assembly (0.2mm recommended for FDM printers)

Peg Assignment - Choose which part gets the male/female joint

Generate

Click "Generate Joints"

Two new objects are created in a [ModelName]_Parts collection

Original mesh is hidden (kept as backup)

Export for Printing

Select each part and export separately as STL

Print, assemble, and enjoy!

